<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 9:45AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...SHOWERS WILL AFFECT EASTERN ROCKINGHAM...CASWELL...SOUTHERN
PITTSYLVANIA AND SOUTHWESTERN HALIFAX COUNTIES AND THE CITY OF
DANVILLE...
At 944 AM EDT, a band of showers was located near Quick, or near
Camp Springs, moving northeast at 35 mph.
Winds in excess of 40 mph are possible with these showers.
Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Eden...
Reidsville...
Wentworth...
Yanceyville...
Bethel...
and Chatham.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
